Package: EpiLPS
Type: Package
Title: EpiLPS: a Fast and Flexible Bayesian Tool for Near Real-Time Estimation
 of the Time-Varying Reproduction Number
Version: 1.0.1
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Authors@R: c(person("Oswaldo","Gressani", 
 email="oswaldo_gressani@hotmail.fr", role=c("aut","cre"),
 comment="Author"))
Maintainer: Oswaldo Gressani <oswaldo_gressani@hotmail.fr>
Description: This package uses Laplacian-P-splines for estimating the
 instantaneous reproduction number R. The negative Binomial distribution is 
 used to model the time series of case counts per unit of time. Two methods are 
 available for fitting R: (1) a fully sampling-free approach based on a 
 maximum a posteriori calibration of the hyperparameter vector and (2) a fully 
 stochastic approach with a Metropolis-within-Gibbs algorithm and
 Langevin diffusions for efficient sampling of the posterior distribution.
URL: <https://github.com/oswaldogressani/EpiLPS>
